# ClickHouse SQL Conventions

## Database: `otel`

## Core Tables

| Table | Engine | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `otel_traces` | MergeTree | Spans — TraceId, SpanId, SpanName, Duration, SpanAttributes, ResourceAttributes |
| `otel_logs` | MergeTree | Logs — TraceId, Body, SeverityText, LogAttributes, ResourceAttributes |
| `otel_metrics_gauge` | MergeTree | Gauge metrics |
| `stack_trace_events` | MergeTree | Symbolicated + grouped stack traces |

## Key Columns in `otel_traces`

`TraceId`, `SpanId`, `ParentSpanId`, `SpanName`, `SpanKind`, `ServiceName`, `Duration` (nanoseconds), `StatusCode`, `StatusMessage`, `SpanAttributes` (Map), `ResourceAttributes` (Map), `Timestamp` (DateTime64)

## Pulse-Specific Attributes

Accessed via `SpanAttributes['key']`:
- `pulse.type`, `pulse.interaction.name`, `pulse.screen.name`
- `app.version`, `os.type`, `device.model.name`

## Schema Conventions

- Use `MergeTree` engine with `ORDER BY` tuples for efficient range queries
- Partition by date for time-series data
- `DateTime64(9)` for nanosecond timestamps
- Map columns for flexible attributes

## Query Rules

- Always include time-range filter on `Timestamp`
- Use `LIMIT` on all queries
- Prefer `toDateTime64()` for timestamp comparisons
